## Data

For this analysis we'll use the penguins dataset from the palmerpenguins package.



::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
library(tidyverse)
library(ggthemes)
library(palmerpenguins)
library(gt)
```
:::



## Species

The figure below is a bar plot of species of penguins.



::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(
  penguins,
  aes(
    x = bill_length_mm, y = bill_depth_mm,
    color = species, shape = species
  )
) +
  geom_point() +
  scale_color_colorblind() +
  labs(x = "Bill length (mm)", y = "Bill depth (mm)") +
  theme_minimal()
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](hello-penguins_files/figure-html/bill-dims-species-1.png){width=480}
:::
:::



## Penguins

The table below shows the first 10 penguins from the dataset.



::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
penguins |>
  slice_head(n = 10) |>
  select(species, island, bill_length_mm, bill_depth_mm) |>
  gt()
```

